Date:12/14/2010 5:58:53 AM
From:Wallace Rivers
It's been a while since I've done a lot of DD on this asset class.
As I understand these products, most invest in senior loans of a very short
maturity. Thus, the risk implied in leverage is lessened, as the portfolio
resets frequently at prevailing interest rates.
Another poster mentioned company specific risk, and examining credit quality.
Each fund is diversified, which mitigates risk to some degree. As these loans
are "senior", they stand at or near the front of the line in the event a
company were to have financial duress.
