Date:12/14/2010 10:24:03 AM
From:Mark Marcellus
what approach does he advocate if you own them in a tax free account?

No difference. That's the holding period they based their research on, so
that's the one that they recommend. Of course anyone is free to do what they
want re holding periods, or anything else, but they're on their own. If you
follow the MF method as put forth by Greenblatt, you adjust at one year
intervals.
